Pre-Game Insights: Harambee Stars Head Coach Engin Firat is exploring injury alternatives for the AFCON qualifier against Zimbabwe.
Collins Sichenje, Ayub Timbe, and Masud Juma have been ruled out of the qualifier.
Michael Olunga is doubtful and scheduled to undergo an MRI scan.
Daniel Anyembe is away for personal reasons.
Firat plans to invite two players from England, Australia, and Ireland but faces logistical challenges due to Kenya’s passport and immigration procedures.
Firat remains optimistic about the upcoming fixtures, aiming for at least four points from the first two matches.
Players are still recovering from preparatory work and may not be at their peak fitness levels yet.
The team is aware of the strength of their opponents, especially Zimbabwe and Namibia.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The team is preparing for a crucial match against Zimbabwe on September 6th, 2024, at Stade Mandela National Stadium in Uganda.
This will be followed by a match against Namibia in South Africa.
Harambee Stars secured a 2-0 victory over Zimbabwe in the COSAFA Cup on July 2, 2024, and a 3-0 win in a World Friendly International on March 26, 2024.
The team’s ultimate success will depend on their performance throughout the entire campaign.
